# DK cross-validation fixtures are byte-exact references compared via
# `cmp` against pak-extracted payloads. Without `-text` here, git's
# autocrlf on Windows checkout would munge LF -> CRLF in notes.txt,
# changing its on-disk byte count from 33 to 34 and breaking the
# bats real-fixture test. The packed `user.pak` is binary regardless;
# pinning it explicitly defends against any future autocrlf default
# change.
test/fixtures/dk/user.pak binary
test/fixtures/dk/inputs/* -text
